name: BGTaskScheduler.Error
desc: The Errors for the BGTaskSchedulerError domain.

items.name: enum BGTaskScheduler.Error.Code
items.desc: An enumeration of the task scheduling errors.

items.name: static var notPermitted: BGTaskScheduler.Error.Code
items.desc: A task scheduling error indicating the app isn’t permitted to launch the task.

items.name: static var tooManyPendingTaskRequests: BGTaskScheduler.Error.Code
items.desc: A task scheduling error indicating that there are too many pending tasks of the type requested.

items.name: static var unavailable: BGTaskScheduler.Error.Code
items.desc: A task scheduling error indicating that the app or extension can’t schedule background work.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A string containing the localized description of the error.

items.name: var errorUserInfo: [String : Any]
items.desc: An NSDictionary containing additional details about the error.

items.name: static var errorDomain: String
items.desc: The background tasks error domain as a string.

items.name: static func == (BGTaskScheduler.Error, BGTaskScheduler.Error) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating if two background tasks errors are equal.

items.name: static func != (BGTaskScheduler.Error, BGTaskScheduler.Error) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating if two background tasks errors are not equal.
